HEADWORD: Yeast-bitten
<hw>Yeast"-bit`ten</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <fld>(Brewing)</fld>
<def>A term used of beer when the froth of the yeast has reentered the
body of the beer.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

